Given an array of integers, replace all the occurrences of elemToReplace with
sustitutionElem.

- Example
  For inputArray = [1, 2, 1], elemToReplace = 1, and substitutionElm = 3,
  the output should be arrayReplace(inputArray, sustitutionElm) = [3, 2, 3]

- Input / Output
  - [execution time limit] 0.5 sec (cpp)

  - [input]
    - array.integer inputArray
    - vector<int> for C Plus Plus
  
    - Guaranteed constraints:
      0 <= inputArray.length <= 10^4
      0 <= inputArray[i] <= 10^9

    - integer elemToReplace
    - Guaranteed constraints:
      0 <= elemToReplace <= 10^9

    - integer substitutionElm
    - Guaranteed constraints
      0 <= substitutionElm <= 10^9


  - [output]
    array.integer
